ZH: 这个珍贵的文物是一位考古学家在战场上发现的战利品。
EN: This precious artifact is a war trophy discovered by an archaeologist on the battlefield.

ZH: 战场上的战利品被带回国家博物馆展示。
EN: The war trophies from the battlefield were brought back to the national museum for display.

ZH: 士兵们会因为争夺战利品而打得你死我活。
EN: Soldiers would fight fiercely for war trophies, even risking their lives.

ZH: 战利品通常是敌方军队所拥有的武器、装备或其他宝贵物品。
EN: War trophies usually consist of weapons, equipment, or other valuable items owned by the enemy army.

ZH: 在古代，人们常把敌方首领的头颅作为战利品进行展示。
EN: In ancient times, people often displayed the heads of enemy leaders as war trophies.

ZH: 他用自己的血肉之躯换来了一片战利品。
EN: He exchanged his own flesh and blood for a piece of war trophy.

ZH: 战利品的价值常常超过战争本身的目标。
EN: The value of war trophies often exceeds the objectives of the war itself.

ZH: 战利品的收集可以带来先祖的荣耀和勇气的象征。
EN: The collection of war trophies can symbolize the glory and courage of ancestors.

ZH: 战利品的归属问题常常引发争议和纠纷。
EN: The issue of the ownership of war trophies often sparks controversy and disputes.

ZH: 他出售了一些珍贵的战争战利品来筹集资金。
EN: He sold some precious war trophies to raise funds.

ZH: 这个博物馆收藏了来自世界各地的战争战利品。
EN: This museum collects war trophies from all around the world.

ZH: 这位老兵一辈子都以自己在战场上获得的战利品为荣。
EN: This veteran is proud of the war trophies he obtained on the battlefield throughout his life.

ZH: 这些战利品见证了一段历史的往事。
EN: These war trophies bear witness to a chapter of history.

ZH: 他对每个战利品背后的故事都了如指掌。
EN: He knows the story behind each war trophy like the back of his hand.

ZH: 部队的士气会因为获取到战利品而大幅提升。
EN: The morale of the troops will greatly increase when they obtain war trophies.

ZH: 这些战利品用来表彰勇敢的士兵和英勇的行为。
EN: These war trophies are used to honor brave soldiers and heroic acts.

ZH: 随着时间的推移，战利品寓意的变化也会发生。
EN: Over time, the symbolism of war trophies also changes.

ZH: 他对收藏不同类型的战利品有着浓厚的兴趣。
EN: He has a strong interest in collecting different types of war trophies.

ZH: 这架战机是敌军飞行员的战利品，他成功地将其击落。
EN: This fighter jet is a war trophy from an enemy pilot, whom he successfully shot down.
